    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1971-12-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1971-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="263"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                <head>263. Memorandum From the Executive Director of the Council on International
                    Economic Policy (<persName corresp="#p_PPG1">Peterson</persName>)<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d263fn1">Source: Washington National Records Center,
                        Department of the Treasury, Files of Under Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_VPA1">Volcker</persName>: <gloss target="#t_FRC1"
                            >FRC</gloss> 56 79 A 15, National Advisory Committee. No classification
                        marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1971-12-28">December 28, 1971</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>MEMORANDUM FOR</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Treasury</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Agriculture</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Commerce</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Labor</item>
                    <item>Ambassador-at-Large <persName corresp="#p_KDM1">David M.
                            Kennedy</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>The Director, Office of Management &amp; Budget</item>
                    <item>The Chairman, Council of Economic Advisers</item>
                    <item>The Special Representative of Trade Negotiation</item>
                    <item>The Assistant to the President for Domestic Affairs</item>
                    <item>The Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Council on International Economic Policy Meeting Monday, January 3, 1972,
                        10:00 A.M.</item>
                </list>
                <pb facs="0697" n="671" xml:id="pg_671"/>
                <p>The President has directed that a meeting of the Council on International
                    Economic Policy be held on Monday, January 3, in the Cabinet Room.</p>
                <p>At this meeting, we shall review trade and investment legislative strategy for
                    1972; the overall legislative climate; the priorities of other domestic
                    legislation as well as the possible relationship of this other domestic
                    legislation to trade and investment legislation; progress on our work programs
                    that might lead to legislation; and the various substantive and timing options
                    we may have before us.</p>
                <p>A review group session of the Council on International Economic Policy was held
                    on this subject earlier this month.<note n="2" xml:id="d263fn2">December
                        10.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Prior to the meeting, an agenda discussing some of the issues and options will be
                    sent to you.</p>
                <p>The meeting will be convened at 10:00 A.M. and is expected to end at 11:00
                    A.M.</p>
                <p>The President has directed that, in his absence,<note n="3" xml:id="d263fn3">The
                        President was scheduled to be in San Clemente to prepare for the Summit with
                        Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_SE3">Sato</persName>.</note> Secretary
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWP1">Rogers</persName> should chair the meeting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">P.P.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
